. The title of the entire volume would then be PERFECTION, which I think is more pleasing.

I would appreciate if you could confirm to me this exchange of titles and positions.





Cordially yours,

Vladimir Nabokov





TO: ANDREW FIELD

TL (XEROX), 1 p.





Montreux-Palace Hotel

1820 Montreux, Switzerland

May 25, 1973

